Package: neuralsbi
Title: Neural Simulation-Based Inference in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("neural.sbi", "authors", email = "plima@rand.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A native R implementation of neural simulation-based inference,
    focused on Neural Posterior Estimation (NPE). Given a prior over
    parameters and a simulator, 'neuralsbi' trains a conditional neural
    density estimator to approximate the Bayesian posterior, enabling
    amortized, likelihood-free inference. The design mirrors the workflow of
    the Python 'sbi' package but is implemented directly in R (using the
    'torch' back end for neural density estimators) rather than wrapping
    Python. It targets applied researchers who want an approachable interface
    with sensible defaults and built-in posterior diagnostics.
